      "is_optimal": false,
      "approve": true,
      "feedback": "The plan correctly unmasks, starts (when appropriate), and enables auditd, which will resolve the vulnerability. Adding applicability checks and verification steps would make it more robust.",
      "concerns": [
        "If auditd package is not installed, the commands will fail.",
        "Running 'systemctl start' without confirming the system is online could cause errors in some edge cases."
      ],
      "suggested_improvements": [
        "Check that the auditd package is installed before attempting to unmask/start/enable (e.g., rpm -q audit || dpkg -l auditd).",
        "Use the full path to systemctl (e.g., /usr/bin/systemctl) to avoid PATH issues.",
        "Verify the service status after starting/enabling (systemctl is-active auditd.service).",
        "Consider wrapping commands in a conditional block similar to the provided script to handle offline systems gracefully."
      ],
      "security_score": 8,
      "best_practices_followed": true
    },
    {
      "finding_id": "service_auditd_enabled",
      "is_optimal": false,
      "approve": true,
      "feedback": "The plan correctly ensures the audit package is present, enables and starts auditd, and verifies its status, addressing most prior concerns. Minor gaps remain (masked service handling and offline\u2011system check).",
      "concerns": [
        "If auditd is masked, enable --now will fail without an explicit unmask step",
        "The script does not check whether the system is in an offline state before starting the service, which could produce errors in rescue or maintenance modes"
      ],
      "suggested_improvements": [
        "Add a step to unmask auditd.service before enabling it (e.g., /usr/bin/systemctl unmask auditd.service)",
        "Wrap the enable/start command in a conditional that checks if the system is online (e.g., compare $(/usr/bin/systemctl is-system-running) to \"offline\")",
